      <chapter eId="chp_226">
        <num>226</num>
        <heading>Prepared Food and Beverage Tax</heading>
        <section eId="sec_12_578d">
          <num>12-578d</num>
          <heading>Presence of minors and employment of young adults at casino gaming facility</heading>
          <subsection eId="12_578d__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>For the purposes of this section, “alcoholic liquor” has the same meaning as provided in section30-1.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="12_578d__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Except as provided in subsection</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="12_578d__subsec_c">
            <num>(c)</num>
            <content>
              <p>of this section, no person under the minimum age for the purchase of alcoholic liquor under the provisions of chapter 545 shall be admitted onto the gaming floor of any casino gaming facility nor be permitted to participate in any authorized games.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="12_578d__subsec_c">
            <num>(c)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A person eighteen years of age or older but under the minimum age for the purchase of alcoholic liquor may be employed in a casino gaming facility, provided such person is licensed by the commissioner pursuant to section12-578cand such employment does not involve handling or serving alcoholic liquor.
(Return to ChapterTable of Contents)(Return toList of Chapters)(Return toList of Titles)</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
      </chapter>
